<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,863,1009]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,903,929]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the island of Luzon where the 
<typeStatus box="[1105,1156,903,929]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
locality situated. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,943,969]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Remarks.</emphasis>
The female specimen is designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[830,932,943,969]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">holotype</typeStatus>
because the male is in poor condition and its genitalia partly damaged.
</paragraph>
